From a81847cdd2fb646e3cbdf271b7625ad7ef3f0a30 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 16:08:52 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Workbench shell: pin Extensions view container in activity
 bar
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 9 step 7 was marked done as "no-op — upstream activity bar
already ships it", but Extensions wasn't actually appearing on the
rail. The cause: `workbench.activity.pinnedViewlets2` (the cached
pinned-view-containers state) didn't include Extensions, so the
activity bar treated it as unpinned.

Added a small workbench contribution that on Restored phase reads
the cached state and ensures Extensions is present + pinned +
visible. Idempotent — leaves an existing entry alone unless it was
explicitly hidden, in which case we re-pin it. Existing customizations
to other view containers (Files, Search, SCM, Run/Debug, etc.) are
preserved.
---
 .../browser/chrome/krtChrome.contribution.ts  | 61 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 61 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/chrome/krtChrome.contribution.ts b/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/chrome/krtChrome.contribution.ts
index 8e9641309fb..2b8187ce1a1 100644
--- a/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/chrome/krtChrome.contribution.ts
+++ b/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/chrome/krtChrome.contribution.ts
@@ -3,10 +3,15 @@
